ggplot(data,aes(x=crit,y=rating)) +
  geom_point() +
  theme_minimal() +
  facet_wrap(~participant)

Calculate performance and fit paramorphic model per participant

# create vector with a list of participants
participants=unique(data$participant)

# prepare data.frame that will contain all results
results=data.frame(participant=participants,
                   achievement=NA,
                   responselinearity=NA,
                   bootstrapping=NA,
                   weight1=NA,
                   weight2=NA,
                   weight3=NA,
                   weight4=NA,
                   stringsAsFactors=F)

for (counter in 1:length(participants))
{
  # select data for a participant
  subdata=subset(data,participant==participants[counter])

  # run the linear regression model
  model_bootstrap=lm(rating~-1+Data+Language+Social+Experience,data=subdata)

  # obtain model predictions
  prediction=predict(model_bootstrap,newdata=subdata) 
  
  # save model predictions in data
  data[data$participant==participants[counter],"pred"]=prediction
  
  # Estimate ACHIEVEMENT (ra)
  results[counter,"achievement"]=cor(subdata$crit,subdata$rating)
  
  # Estimate RESPONSE LINEARITY/CONSISTENCY (Rs)
  results[counter,"responselinearity"]=cor(subdata$rating,prediction)
  
  # Estimate BOOTSTRAPPING (GRe)
  results[counter,"bootstrapping"]=cor(subdata$crit,prediction)
  
  # Save WEIGHTS
  results[counter,c("weight1","weight2","weight3","weight4")]=coef(model_bootstrap)
  
}
